==Portuguese==

===Etymology===
Latin ''[[paucus]]''

===Pronunciation===
/ˈpowku/

===Pronoun===
'''pouco''' ''m sing'', '''poucos''' ''m plural'', '''pouca''' ''f sing'', '''poucas''' ''f plural''

# [[little]], [[few]]
: ''Muito poucos vieram.'' Very few came.

===Adjective===
'''pouco''' ''m sing'', '''poucos''' ''m plural'', '''pouca''' ''f sing'', '''poucas''' ''f plural''

# [[little]], not [[much]]; [[few]], not [[many]]
: ''Poucas pessoas acreditam nisso.'' Not many poeple believe it.

===Adverb===
'''pouco''' ''adv''

# not [[much]], not [[very]] <br> : ''Ele lê pouco.'' He doesn't read much.
# not [[long]] <br> : ''Eles saíram há pouco.'' They left not long ago.
# '''um pouco''' a [[little]] <br> : ''Espere um pouco.'' Wait a little.


